        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>At a special meeting of the Board of Hebrew Ministers held<lb/> this day&#44; the following preamble and resolutions were unanimously<lb/> adopted.<lb/></p>
            <p>Whereas the Lord that &#34;bringeth down to the grave and bringeth up&#44;&#34;<lb/> willed that Judaism be bereft of one of its most zealous defenders&#44;<lb/> and we of a learned coadjutor&#44; therefore<lb/></p>
            <p>Resolved that we mourn&#8212;with the Hebrew Communities of<lb/> America&#45;&#45;<del>over</del> so the irreparable loss sustained by the death of<lb/> the Revd Isaac Leeser.<lb/></p>
            <p>Resolved that by this sorrowful occurrence&#44; our Board is deprived<lb/> of the kind offices of a Secretary ever active and experienced.<lb/></p>
            <p>Resolved that as an evidence of the high esteem in which the<lb/> deceased was held&#44; we will accompany his mortal remains to<lb/> their final destination.<lb/></p>
            <p>Resolved that&#44; as by reason of a testamentary request&#44; we are<lb/> denied the gratification of eulogizing <del></del> the death of&#93; our col&#45;<lb/>&#61;league&#44; while yet unburied&#44; we will early exhibit his goodly<lb/> deeds before our respective congregation.<lb/></p>
            <p>Resolved that the favor of the Editors of our various Jewish<lb/> periodicals is hereby asked for an insertion of the proceedings of<lb/> this meeting.<lb/></p>
            <p>Philadelphia Shebat 9<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 5628. S. Morais. Sec. p. t.<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Resolved that the members of the Board&#8212;having<lb/> always regarded the Red Isaac Leeser&#44; as the man<lb/> whose energies were solely and effectually devoted to<lb/> the spread of religious education&#44; and whose unwearied<lb/> zeal resulted in the establishing and success of our school&#45;&#45;<lb/> are unable to adequately express the sorrow experienced<lb/> at his death.<lb/></p>
            <p>Resolved that&#8212;which believing that he whose <sic>undefet&#45;<lb/>&#45;gable</sic> endeavours aimed at the elevation of his poeple<lb/> and the glory of his God&#44; is now reaping a harvest<lb/> of joy&#44; they still bemoan the loss of a colleague&#44; so<lb/> bright in intellect&#44; and so wise in counsel.<lb/></p>
            <p>Resolved that as a testimonial of the respect in which the<lb/> renowned scholar&#44; now removed from earth was held&#44;<lb/> the school shall be closed until he be buried&#44; and that<lb/> the members of this Board will attend his funeral as<lb/> a body.<lb/></p>
            <p>Resolved that the foregoing resolutions be published<lb/> in the Occident &#38; in all Jewish periodicals throughout<lb/> the United States of America.<lb/></p>
            
        </body>
